title: Laeticia Amihere
text:
Laeticia Amihere (born July 10, 2001) is a Canadian <a href="basketball">basketball</a> player in the <a href="Forward%20%28basketball%29">forward</a> position. 
Career.
Amihere has won gold at the <a href="2015%20FIBA%20Americas%20Under-16%20Championship%20for%20Women">2015 FIBA Americas Under-16 Championship for Women</a> as part of the junior team, and then bronze at the <a href="2017%20FIBA%20Under-19%20Women%27s%20Basketball%20World%20Cup">2017 FIBA Under-19 Women's Basketball World Cup</a>. Amihere is currently playing with the <a href="South%20Carolina%20Gamecocks%20women%27s%20basketball">South Carolina Gamecocks women's basketball</a> team.
In July 2021, Amihere was named to <a href="Canada%20at%20the%202020%20Summer%20Olympics">Canada's 2020 Olympic team</a>.
